    <p> At the end of today, there was a special visit to the beach on the piece of beach. A few km before you get to the sea lions, there is a bay in which you can watch the penguins come home. The beach itself is of course cordoned off and some stands built up so that the crowds can also see something. At the sunset, three rangers appeared and stood at the foot of the stands and told us a little about the penguins and that it was strictly forbidden to take photos and film. Which of course puked us up quite a bit. Because even photos without lightning are forbidden. It would disturb the animals!?! (Mind you without flash !!!) </p>
    <p> In the end it didn't matter, since in most cases the penguins were only recognizable as shadows that scurried over the beach. After some animals were shushing over the beach, we slowly made our way back and found that the paths of the penguins went along the hiking path and then we still had one or the other option to take a photo (without lightning, of course) or to take the shouting of the young animals. </p>
    <p> When we arrived at the parking lot, we made another check that no penguin sits under the car before we went back to the campsite. This time Steffi fell asleep again on the expressways. </p>
    <p> When we finally arrived at the campsite again, we only watched that we were coming to bed. After all, tomorrow should be a long day again. </p>
    <p> Good night. </p>
